 interest to students and scholars of Russian literature, Tolstoy, symbol, allegory, structuralism, and moral criticism.  afunded by National Endowment for the Humanities and The Andrew W. Mellon Foundation Humanities Open Book Program  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh2 aNational Endowment for the Humanities and The Andrew W. Mellon Foundation Humanities Open Book Programefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package Backlist 2008-2015z978311068814640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618116796zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618116796.jpg  a978-3-11-068814-6 ASP eBook Package Backlist 2008-2015c2008d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA